We have simulated a number of network structures, focusing on those with diagonalizable W matrix, and investigated the effect of some parameters on opinion dynamics. Due to space limitations, we present three simulations that illustrate in Figures 1, 2, and 3 the results of Theorems 1, 2 and Proposition 1. Here, we confine our investigation of parameter effects to only see what happens if the control term in the cost function is dominant or not dominant. The simulation results in Figures 1 and 2 coincide with the plots obtained by the analytic expressions of the opinion trajectories from Theorems 1 and 2. In all simulations, number of agents is and terminal time is units. Initial opinion levels of the agents are chosen as .
